Reverting to an old word order. (Photo by Drew Angerer/Getty Images)

On election night, I attended a party for political consultants visiting from over 40 countries to observe the U.S. election. I had moderated a panel a few hours earlier with experts from a half dozen of these countries, discussing what the presidential election would mean to the rest of the globe. It appeared to me very early that Donald Trump was going to win, and as I was preparing to leave I found myself alone with a gentleman from my earlier panel
